    "urn": "urn:li:activity:7110636607551979520",
    "text": "German-Austrian Healthcare Forum: The future of health care in #austria, #slovenia and #germany.\nThe event took place on 19th September at the Grand Union Hotel in Ljubljana and co-organized by German-Slovene Chamber of Commerce and Industry (AHK Slowenien) and ADVANTAGE AUSTRIA Slovenia.\n\nIn her opening address, Ms. Dagmar von Bohnstein, President of the German-Slovene Chamber of Commerce and Industry (AHK Slowenien), emphasized the vital economic ties between Slovenia and Germany and their impact on healthcare systems. Mr. Wilhelm Nest, Director of ADVANTAGE AUSTRIA Slovenia, stressed the significance of accessible healthcare based on personal experience, and Dr. Alenka Kolar, Director General of the Directorate for Digitalization in Healthcare at the Ministry of Health, briefly outlined Slovenia's healthcare history and key challenges Ministry faces.\n\nThis was followed by brief presentations on the functioning of health systems, their specificities, and the challenges they face in Germany (Dr. Philipp Wien from the German Chamber of Commerce and Industry DIHK), Austria (Dr. Alexander Biach, Deputy Head of the Vienna Chamber of Commerce and Industry) and Slovenia (Dr. Petra Do≈°enoviƒá Bonƒça, Associate Professor at the University of Ljubljana, School of Economics and Business in Ljubljana), as well as a roundtable discussion with all the speakers.\n\nParticipants also gained insights from Ms. Lotta Westerlund, Deputy Managing Director of the AHK Finnland (German-Finnish Chamber of Commerce), regarding the Finnish healthcare system as a digital healthcare best practice. This was followed by brief presentations of digital healthcare solutions from Germany and Austria, including Elke Zens from ilvi - smart health solutions, Jakob Pieber from PH Predicting Health GmbH and Tanja ≈†tamec from Hagleitner Hygiene International GmbH.\n\nIn the panel's conclusion, Moderator Tjasa Zajc spotlighted challenges within Slovenia's healthcare sector, joined by panelists Barbara Stegel, Secretary General of the International Forum of Scientific Research Pharmaceutical Companies, Mateja Lencic from Merkur Versicherung, and Tanja ≈†tamec from Hagleitner Hygiene International GmbH.\n\nThe discussion on health systems in Slovenia, Germany and Austria was attended by about 75 participants and moderated by Tja≈°a Zajc, an internationally renowned expert in digital health.\n\nWe would like to thank all the panelists, speakers and everyone who attended the event.\n\nDon't miss the highlights of the event in the photo gallery below and on our website: https://lnkd.in/e6cVCTPJ\n\n#healtcare #healthcareslovenia #healthcaregermany #healthcareaustria",
